In the face of soaring human pressures and habitat loss, Rwandan vet and conservationist Olivier Nsengimana has used a wildlife management plan grounded in the encouragement of his young compatriots to ensure the preservation of the regal grey crowned crane. These magnificent birds, traditionally held captive in gardens of the country’s wealthy, are flourishing and the 2014 Rolex Awards for Enterprise Laureate’s work is becoming a symbol of African renewal.
Discover more on.rolex.org/Olivier-Nsengimana

#Rolex #PerpetualPlanet #RolexAwards

Ophthalmologist Andrew Bastawrous set up Peek Vision to deliver eye care for populations that need it most but have the least access to it. Thanks in part to his 2016 Rolex Award for Enterprise, he developed the Peek Acuity app which has delivered more than 350,000 eye tests to people in rural Kenya and is expanding to multiple locations across Africa and Asia.
Discover more on.rolex.org/Andrew-Bastawrous
#Rolex #PerpetualPlanet #RolexAwards

node.title: A vision for universal eye care

Through Rolex’s Perpetual Planet initiative, @mission_blue and Rolex have joined forces and resources in the name of the oceans. Mission Blue’s way lights the spark of community spirit to encourage people living in places that are vital to the health and future of the seas to fight for their protection. Magically named ‘Hope Spots’ by the organization's founder Sylvia Earle, these sanctuaries of marine life are found scattered in the immensity of the Earth's Blue Heart.
Discover more on.rolex.org/Mission-Blue

#Rolex #PerpetualPlanet #HopeSpots

Environmental anthropologist Shafqat Hussain has used his 2006 Rolex Award for Enterprise to further the development of his Project Snow Leopard. The scheme compensates herders and shepherds for the loss of livestock caused by the predator and teaches villagers how to construct leopard-proof shelters for their flock.
Discover more on.rolex.org/Shafqat-Hussain

A masterpiece is a celebration of humanity’s creativity which remains relevant regardless of how many years go by. This incendiary force for change does not lose its power, ever. For close to a century, Rolex and the Oscars have respectively been behind masterpieces in watchmaking and filmmaking that capture moments in time, unleash raw emotion and inspire people to see the world through a new lens. As partner of the Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences and Proud Sponsor of the Oscars®, we share a common quest to produce seamless blends of arts and science that stand the test of time.

#Rolex #Oscars #Perpetual

node.text:
In 2006 Australian marine scientist Brad Norman received a Rolex Award for Enterprise to advance his pioneering system of monitoring endangered whale sharks, the world’s biggest fish. Drawing on an algorithm developed by NASA, his project identifies and follows the sharks based on their unique markings. The project is emblematic of Rolex’s Perpetual Planet initiative to help protect the natural world. Norman is accompanied by his reliable Submariner on all his diving expeditions.
#Rolex #Submariner #PerpetualPlanet

node.text:
@alexzverev123 is reaching new heights in a burgeoning career. He has fulfilled his childhood dream of playing on the world’s biggest tennis stages and earning his place among the very best in the men’s elite. The German champion has made his mark on the game, winning more than a dozen titles – including the end-of-year ATP Tour Finals in 2018 and four ATP Masters 1000 tournaments – while being a permanent fixture in the world’s top 10 since 2017. A first Grand Slam® final appearance at the 2020 US Open was evidence that he had truly arrived. Zverev derives a sense of achievement from being the best version of himself and having the drive to pursue what means most to him. Rolex is pleased to count him among its Testimonees.

@belindabencic is achieving the success for which she has always seemed destined. Marked for greatness from an early age, she has established herself among the best in the women’s ranks through a combination of irrepressible talent and sheer determination. Having reached the 2014 US Open quarter-finals at 17, the Swiss star displayed impressive mental fortitude by not allowing a series of injuries to derail her from fulfilling her potential. She returned to form in 2019 when she made it to her first Grand Slam® semi-final at the US Open, won two titles, reached the last four of the season-ending WTA Finals and then climbed to fourth in the world rankings in early 2020. For Bencic, achievement is about doing everything in her power to win and ensure her hard work is rewarded. Rolex is delighted to have her in its family of Testimonees.

node.text:
From 1945 to 2021, and beyond. The Datejust revolutionized wristwatch date display when it was launched, introducing a calendar that presented the date via a disc in a window at 3 o’clock. This would become the watchmaking standard. The Datejust has spanned eras, evolving technically while retaining the enduring aesthetic characteristics that make it so instantly recognizable. The evolution continues.
#Rolex #Datejust #Perpetual
